moapy.unit_converter.name: assertAlmostEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Fail if the two objects are unequal as determined by their
difference rounded to the given number of decimal places
(default 7) and comparing to zero, or by comparing that the
difference between the two objects is more than the given
delta.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertCountEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Asserts that two iterables have the same elements, the same number of
times, without regard to order.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Fail if the two objects are unequal as determined by the '=='
operator.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertFalse
moapy.unit_converter.description: Check that the expression is false.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertGreater
moapy.unit_converter.description: Just like self.assertTrue(a > b), but with a nicer default message.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertGreaterEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description: Just like self.assertTrue(a >= b), but with a nicer default message.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertIn
moapy.unit_converter.description: Just like self.assertTrue(a in b), but with a nicer default message.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertIs
moapy.unit_converter.description: Just like self.assertTrue(a is b), but with a nicer default message.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertIsInstance
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Same as self.assertTrue(isinstance(obj, cls)), with a nicer
default message.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertIsNone
moapy.unit_converter.description: Same as self.assertTrue(obj is None), with a nicer default message.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertIsNot
moapy.unit_converter.description: Just like self.assertTrue(a is not b), but with a nicer default message.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertIsNotNone
moapy.unit_converter.description: Included for symmetry with assertIsNone.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertLess
moapy.unit_converter.description: Just like self.assertTrue(a < b), but with a nicer default message.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertLessEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description: Just like self.assertTrue(a <= b), but with a nicer default message.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertListEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description: A list-specific equality assertion.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertLogs
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Fail unless a log message of level *level* or higher is emitted
on *logger_name* or its children.  If omitted, *level* defaults to
INFO and *logger* defaults to the root logger.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertMultiLineEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description: Assert that two multi-line strings are equal.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertNoLogs
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Fail unless no log messages of level *level* or higher are emitted
on *logger_name* or its children.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertNotAlmostEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Fail if the two objects are equal as determined by their
difference rounded to the given number of decimal places
(default 7) and comparing to zero, or by comparing that the
difference between the two objects is less than the given delta.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertNotEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Fail if the two objects are equal as determined by the '!='
operator.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertNotIn
moapy.unit_converter.description: Just like self.assertTrue(a not in b), but with a nicer default message.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertNotIsInstance
moapy.unit_converter.description: Included for symmetry with assertIsInstance.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertNotRegex
moapy.unit_converter.description: Fail the test if the text matches the regular expression.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertRaises
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Fail unless an exception of class expected_exception is raised
by the callable when invoked with specified positional and
keyword arguments. If a different type of exception is
raised, it will not be caught, and the test case will be
deemed to have suffered an error, exactly as for an
unexpected exception.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertRaisesRegex
moapy.unit_converter.description: Asserts that the message in a raised exception matches a regex.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertRegex
moapy.unit_converter.description: Fail the test unless the text matches the regular expression.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertSequenceEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description: An equality assertion for ordered sequences (like lists and tuples).

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertSetEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description: A set-specific equality assertion.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertTrue
moapy.unit_converter.description: Check that the expression is true.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertTupleEqual
moapy.unit_converter.description: A tuple-specific equality assertion.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertWarns
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Fail unless a warning of class warnClass is triggered
by the callable when invoked with specified positional and
keyword arguments.  If a different type of warning is
triggered, it will not be handled: depending on the other
warning filtering rules in effect, it might be silenced, printed
out, or raised as an exception.

moapy.unit_converter.name: assertWarnsRegex
moapy.unit_converter.description:
Asserts that the message in a triggered warning matches a regexp.
Basic functioning is similar to assertWarns() with the addition
that only warnings whose messages also match the regular expression
are considered successful matches.

moapy.unit_converter.name: skipTest

moapy.unit_converter.name: subTest
